body_html: @zafartahirov I find the way to install. First all the packages like six, mock update using apt, the python have default installed mock, six but the version is very low(at least in the debian jessie stable), OS will seem ignore the manually updating. Using the apt, installation of tensor(whl) is very easy.

body: @zafartahirov I find the way to install. First all the packages like six, mock update using `apt`, the python have default installed mock, six but the version is very low(at least in the debian jessie stable), OS will seem ignore the manually updating. Using the `apt`, installation of tensor(whl) is very easy.
